frSvcDlcmiTable.name: frSvcDlcmiTable
frSvcDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Switched Virtual Circuit Link Connection Management Interface for the frame relay service on this interface.

frSvcDlcmiEntry.name: frSvcDlcmiEntry
frSvcDlcmiEntry.description: The information regarding a single switched Data Link Connection Management Interface.

frSvcDlcmiIfIndex.name: frSvcDlcmiIfIndex
frSvcDlcmiIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEntry.

frSvcDlcmiState.name: frSvcDlcmiState
frSvcDlcmiState.description: This variable states which Data Link Connection Management scheme is on the Frame Relay switched interface.

frSvcDlcmiMaxNumCalls.name: frSvcDlcmiMaxNumCalls
frSvcDlcmiMaxNumCalls.description: Indicates the maximum number of calls allowed on the interface.

frSvcDlcmiCallSetupTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiCallSetupTimer
frSvcDlcmiCallSetupTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T303.
frSvcDlcmiCallSetupTimer.description: This timer is started when the CALL SETUP message is sent. The timer is stopped when the sender receives a CALL PROCEEDING message. If the timer, expressed in seconds, expires, it is retried once before the call is cleared. The default value is 4 seconds.

frSvcDlcmiCallProceedingTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiCallProceedingTimer
frSvcDlcmiCallProceedingTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T310.
frSvcDlcmiCallProceedingTimer.description: This timer is started when the CALL PROCEEDING message is sent. The timer is stopped when the sender receives a CALL CONNECT message. If the timer, expressed in seconds, expires, the call is cleared. The default value is 10 seconds.

frSvcDlcmiCallDisconnectTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiCallDisconnectTimer
frSvcDlcmiCallDisconnectTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T305.
frSvcDlcmiCallDisconnectTimer.description: This timer is started when the DISCONNECT message is sent. The timer is stopped when the sender receives a RELEASE message. The sender then responds with a RELEASE COMPLETE message. If the timer, expressed in seconds, expires, the sender starts up Timer T308, and sends a RELEASE message. The default value for this timer is 30 seconds.

frSvcDlcmiCallReleaseTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiCallReleaseTimer
frSvcDlcmiCallReleaseTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T308.
frSvcDlcmiCallReleaseTimer.description: This timer is started if timer T305 expires. This timer is stopped when the sender receives a RELEASE message. If the timer, expressed in seconds, expires, the timer sequence is reinitiated. If the timer expires a second time the call is cleared. The default value fo rthis timer is 4 seconds.

frSvcDlcmiStatusEnquiryTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiStatusEnquiryTimer
frSvcDlcmiStatusEnquiryTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T322.
frSvcDlcmiStatusEnquiryTimer.description: This timer is started when a STATUS ENQUIRY message is sent. If a STATUS message is received, the timer will be stopped. If the Timer expires it may be retried an implementation specific number (n) of times. Upon expiry of (n), the call is cleared. The default value is 4 retries.

frSvcDlcmiErrorThreshold.name: frSvcDlcmiErrorThreshold
frSvcDlcmiErrorThreshold.description: This is the implementation specific number of times that the STATUS ENQUIRY Timer, T322, will be retried.

frSvcDlcmiResetSentTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiResetSentTimer
frSvcDlcmiResetSentTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T316.
frSvcDlcmiResetSentTimer.description: This timer is started when a RESTART message is sent. If a RESTART ACKNOWLEDGEmessage is received, the timer will be stopped. If the Timer expires expires it may be retried one or more times until a RESTART ACKNOWLEDGE message is returned. Meanwhile No calls shall be placed or accepted over the interface by the originator of the RESTART message. The network shall limit the number of consecutive unsuccessful attempts to a default of 2. The default value for the Timer is 120 seconds

frSvcDlcmiResetAckTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiResetAckTimer
frSvcDlcmiResetAckTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.931, Section 9.2: Timer T317.
frSvcDlcmiResetAckTimer.description: This timer is started when a RESTART message is received. At this time the receiving entity shall initiate the appropriate internal actions to return the specified interface to the idle condition and call references to the Null state. Upon expiry of the timer, a notification shall be made to the maintenance entity. NOTE: This Timer MUST be less than Timer T316.

frSvcDlcmiIdleTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiIdleTimer
frSvcDlcmiIdleTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.921, Section 5.9 / Q.922 Section 5.9: Timer T203.
frSvcDlcmiIdleTimer.description: This is the maximum time allowed without any frames being exchanged. The default for this timer is 30 seconds.

frSvcDlcmiRetransmissionTimer.name: frSvcDlcmiRetransmissionTimer
frSvcDlcmiRetransmissionTimer.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.921, Section 5.9 / Q.922 Section 5.9: Timer T200.
frSvcDlcmiRetransmissionTimer.description: This is the re-transmission timer. It is started upon transmission of frames. When a response is received, the timer will be shut down. If the timer expires , it may be retried N200 times. When N200 times have been reached, a DL-RELEASE message will be sent to the Layer 3 entity. The default for this timer is 1.5 seconds.

frSvcDlcmiNumRetransmissions.name: frSvcDlcmiNumRetransmissions
frSvcDlcmiNumRetransmissions.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.921, Section 5.9 / Q.922 Section 5.9: N200.
frSvcDlcmiNumRetransmissions.description: This value indicates the number of times T200 timer will be retried. When N200 times have been reached, a DL-RELEASE message will be sent to the Layer 3 entity. The default for this value is 3 retries.

frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFieldSize.name: frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFieldSize
frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFieldSize.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.921, Section 5.9 / Q.922 Section 5.9: N201.
frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFieldSize.description: This value indicates the maximum number of octets in an Information field. The default value is 260 octets.

frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFrames.name: frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFrames
frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFrames.reference: ITU-T Standard Q.921, Section 5.9 / Q.922 Section 5.9: k.
frSvcDlcmiMaxInfoFrames.description: This value indicates the maximum number of sequentially numbered I frames that may be outstanding (that is, unacknowledged) at any given time. This number shall not exceed 127. For a 16Kbps link: k = 3, 64Kbps: k = 7 (this is the default value), 384Kbps: k = 32, 1.5Mbps/1.92Mbps: k = 40.

frSvcDlcmiQ922State.name: frSvcDlcmiQ922State
frSvcDlcmiQ922State.description: This value indicates the state of the Q.922 Point to Point Data Link Layer Negotiation.

frSvcTable.name: frSvcTable
frSvcTable.description: A table containing information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding switched virtual circuits.

frSvcEntry.name: frSvcEntry
frSvcEntry.description: The information regarding a single switched Data Link Connection Identifier.

frSvcIfIndex.name: frSvcIfIndex
frSvcIfIndex.description: The ifIndex Value of the ifEntry this virtual circuit is layered onto.

frSvcDlci.name: frSvcDlci
frSvcDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this virtual circuit.

frSvcReceivedFECNs.name: frSvcReceivedFECNs
frSvcReceivedFECNs.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.3
frSvcReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating forward congestion since the virtual circuit was created.

frSvcReceivedBECNs.name: frSvcReceivedBECNs
frSvcReceivedBECNs.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.4
frSvcReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating backward congestion since the virtual circuit was created.

frSvcSentFrames.name: frSvcSentFrames
frSvcSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

frSvcSentOctets.name: frSvcSentOctets
frSvcSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

frSvcReceivedFrames.name: frSvcReceivedFrames
frSvcReceivedFrames.description: Number of frames received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

frSvcReceivedOctets.name: frSvcReceivedOctets
frSvcReceivedOctets.description: Number of octets received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

frSvcCreationTime.name: frSvcCreationTime
frSvcCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the virtual cir- cuit was created.

frSvcInMaxFmifSize.name: frSvcInMaxFmifSize
frSvcInMaxFmifSize.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of end user data octets in a frame for in the direction of the calling user to the called user. The default value is 262 octets.

frSvcOutMaxFmifSize.name: frSvcOutMaxFmifSize
frSvcOutMaxFmifSize.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of end user data octets in a frame for in the direction of the called user to the calling user. The default value is 262 octets.

frSvcInCommittedBurst.name: frSvcInCommittedBurst
frSvcInCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to accept under normal conditions, during the measurement interval. The default value is 0.

frSvcOutCommittedBurst.name: frSvcOutCommittedBurst
frSvcOutCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval. The default value is 0.

frSvcInExcessBurst.name: frSvcInExcessBurst
frSvcInExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will at- tempt to receive over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

frSvcOutExcessBurst.name: frSvcOutExcessBurst
frSvcOutExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will at- tempt to deliver over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

frSvcInCIR.name: frSvcInCIR
frSvcInCIR.description: CIR is the average number of 'Frame Re- lay Information Field' bits received per second across a user network interface to the calling user, measured over the measurement inter- val. The default value is 0.

frSvcOutCIR.name: frSvcOutCIR
frSvcOutCIR.description: CIR is the average number of 'Frame Re- lay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface from the calling user, measured over the measurement inter- val. The default value is 0.

frSvcInMinCIR.name: frSvcInMinCIR
frSvcInMinCIR.description: Minimum Acceptable CIR is the lowest throughput value, in the direction to the calling user, expressed in bits per second, that the calling user is willing to accept for the call. If the network or the called user is unable to support this throughput, the call will be cleared. The default value is 0.

frSvcOutMinCIR.name: frSvcOutMinCIR
frSvcOutMinCIR.description: Minimum Acceptable CIR is the lowest throughput value, in the direction from the calling user, expressed in bits per second, that the calling user is willing to accept for the call. If the network or the called user is unable to support this throughput, the call will be cleared. The default value is 0.

frSvcState.name: frSvcState
frSvcState.description: Indicates whether the Connection has been completed and data can proceed (2), or if the call setup is still in process (1).

frSvcCallReferenceValue.name: frSvcCallReferenceValue
frSvcCallReferenceValue.description: Indicates the call identity number of the call on the interface.

frSvcCallingAddr.name: frSvcCallingAddr
frSvcCallingAddr.description: Indicates the address of the calling party.

frSvcCallingSubAddr.name: frSvcCallingSubAddr
frSvcCallingSubAddr.description: Indicates the sub-address of the calling party.

frSvcCalledAddr.name: frSvcCalledAddr
frSvcCalledAddr.description: Indicates the address of the called party.

frSvcCalledSubAddr.name: frSvcCalledSubAddr
frSvcCalledSubAddr.description: Indicates the sub-address of the called party.

frSvcCallSetup.name: frSvcCallSetup
frSvcCallSetup.description: Indicates whether the call should be Setup or Disconnected.

frSvcCallOrigination.name: frSvcCallOrigination
frSvcCallOrigination.description: Indicates the direction of the call. identifies the circuit as the calling (local) or the called side (remote).
